---
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  The unified operator interface where staff, supervisors, and agents share a single working environment. Workspace surfaces the right context, tools, and actions for each role — eliminating tab-switching and context loss.
</p>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">What it does</h2>
<ul class="fd-list">
  <li class="fd-list-item">Role-based views: staff see their work, supervisors see team health, agents surface insights</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Contextual patient information available inline — no EHR tab required</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Integrated communication tools: call, text, and video from within the workspace</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Real-time activity feed showing agent actions, task completions, and escalations</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">One interface, every role</h2>
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Workspace replaces the patchwork of tools care teams use today. Staff stay in one place. Supervisors have full visibility. Agents surface their work where humans can act on it.
</p>
